import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# World light
bpy.data.worlds["World"].node_tree.nodes["Background"].inputs[0].default_value = (0.92, 0.92, 0.92, 1)
bpy.data.worlds["World"].node_tree.nodes["Background"].inputs[1].default_value = 0.7

# -----------------------------
# Materials
# -----------------------------
wood_floor = create_principled_material("WoodFloor", base_color=(0.54, 0.40, 0.28, 1), roughness=0.7, specular=0.3)
wood_desk = create_principled_material("WoodDesk", base_color=(0.72, 0.54, 0.33, 1), roughness=0.6, specular=0.35)
mat_wall = create_principled_material("Wall", base_color=(0.96, 0.96, 0.95, 1), roughness=0.9, specular=0.1)
mat_baseboard = create_principled_material("Baseboard", base_color=(0.93, 0.93, 0.93, 1), roughness=0.4, specular=0.2)
mat_black_plastic = create_principled_material("BlackPlastic", base_color=(0.03,0.03,0.03,1), roughness=0.4, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5)
mat_screen = create_principled_material("Screen", base_color=(0.06,0.08,0.1,1), roughness=0.1, specular=0.1)

# -----------------------------
# Room: floor, wall, baseboard
# -----------------------------
# Floor
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,0,0))
floor = bpy.context.active_object
floor.name = "Floor"
floor.data.materials.append(wood_floor)

# Wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,-3,1.5))
wall = bpy.context.active_object
wall.name = "Wall"
wall.rotation_euler = Euler((math.radians(90), 0, 0), 'XYZ')
wall.data.materials.append(mat_wall)

# Baseboard along the wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(0,-2.99,0.06))
baseboard = bpy.context.active_object
baseboard.name = "Baseboard"
baseboard.scale = (4.0, 0.01, 0.06)   # 8m long, 2cm thick, 12cm tall
baseboard.data.materials.append(mat_baseboard)

# -----------------------------
# Desk (simple parametric build)
# -----------------------------
desk_center = Vector((0.0, -1.20, 0.0))
desk_w, desk_d, desk_h = 1.60, 0.75, 0.74
panel_t = 0.04

# Desk top
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_center.y, desk_h + panel_t/2))
desk_top = bpy.context.active_object
desk_top.name = "DeskTop"
desk_top.scale = (desk_w/2, desk_d/2, panel_t/2)
desk_top.data.materials.append(wood_desk)

# Left panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x - (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))
panel_L = bpy.context.active_object
panel_L.name = "DeskPanel_L"
panel_L.scale = (panel_t/2, desk_d/2, desk_h/2)
panel_L.data.materials.append(wood_desk)

# Right panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x + (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))
panel_R = bpy.context.active_object
panel_R.name = "DeskPanel_R"
panel_R.scale = (panel_t/2, desk_d/2, desk_h/2)
panel_R.data.materials.append(wood_desk)

# Modesty panel near the front under the top
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, -0.855, 0.68))
modesty = bpy.context.active_object
modesty.name = "DeskModesty"
modesty.scale = (desk_w/2 - 0.02, 0.01, 0.06)
modesty.data.materials.append(wood_desk)

# -----------------------------
# Simple laptop
# -----------------------------
# Base
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(-0.20, -1.08, desk_h + 0.015/2))
laptop_base = bpy.context.active_object
laptop_base.name = "LaptopBase"
laptop_base.scale = (0.30/2, 0.22/2, 0.015/2)
laptop_base.data.materials.append(mat_black_plastic)

# Screen (thin slab) slightly open
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(-0.20, -1.165, desk_h + 0.015 + 0.20/2))
laptop_screen = bpy.context.active_object
laptop_screen.name = "LaptopScreen"
laptop_screen.scale = (0.30/2, 0.01/2, 0.20/2)
laptop_screen.rotation_euler = Euler((math.radians(100), 0, 0), 'XYZ')
laptop_screen.data.materials.append(mat_screen)

# Hinge accent (optional small cylinder)
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cylinder_add(radius=0.005, depth=0.30, location=(-0.20, -1.155, desk_h + 0.015))
hinge = bpy.context.active_object
hinge.rotation_euler = Euler((0,0,math.radians(90)), 'XYZ')
hinge.data.materials.append(mat_black_plastic)

# -----------------------------
# Import office chair (GLB)
# -----------------------------
import os

chair_path = os.path.normpath("output/demo/blendergym_hard/20250926_170545/assets/office chair.glb")
if os.path.exists(chair_path):
    # Import and group
    bpy.ops.import_scene.gltf(filepath=chair_path)
    imported = bpy.context.selected_objects[:]
    chair_coll = bpy.data.collections.new("OfficeChair")
    bpy.context.scene.collection.children.link(chair_coll)
    for obj in imported:
        # Unlink from root collection and link to chair collection
        if obj.name in bpy.context.scene.collection.objects:
            bpy.context.scene.collection.objects.unlink(obj)
        chair_coll.objects.link(obj)

    # Create an empty to manipulate the whole chair as one
    bpy.ops.object.empty_add(type='PLAIN_AXES', location=(0,0,0))
    chair_empty = bpy.context.active_object
    chair_empty.name = "ChairRig"

    for obj in imported:
        obj.parent = chair_empty

    # Position, rotation, scale
    chair_empty.location = Vector((0.65, -0.55, 0.0))
    chair_empty.rotation_euler = Euler((0, 0, math.radians(-130)), 'XYZ')
    chair_empty.scale = (1.0, 1.0, 1.0)
else:
    print("Chair GLB not found at", chair_path)

# -----------------------------
# Lighting
# -----------------------------
# Big soft area light near camera
bpy.ops.object.light_add(type='AREA', location=(0.7, 2.2, 2.3))
area = bpy.context.active_object
area.data.energy = 1200
area.data.size = 3.0
area.rotation_euler = Euler((math.radians(-60), 0, math.radians(-10)), 'XYZ')

# Secondary fill from left
bpy.ops.object.light_add(type='AREA', location=(-2.2, 1.2, 1.8))
fill = bpy.context.active_object
fill.data.energy = 400
fill.data.size = 2.0
fill.rotation_euler = Euler((math.radians(-55), 0, math.radians(20)), 'XYZ')

# -----------------------------
# Camera
# -----------------------------
bpy.ops.object.camera_add(location=(0.6, 2.7, 1.45))
cam = bpy.context.active_object
cam.data.lens = 50
look_at(cam, Vector((0.0, -1.2, 0.8)))
bpy.context.scene.camera = cam

print("Scene ready.")

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# World light (robust setup even if 'World' is missing)
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    # Remove existing links to Surface to avoid duplicates
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("BSDF"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.92, 0.92, 0.92, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.7

# -----------------------------
# Materials
# -----------------------------
wood_floor = create_principled_material("WoodFloor", base_color=(0.54, 0.40, 0.28, 1), roughness=0.7, specular=0.3)
wood_desk = create_principled_material("WoodDesk", base_color=(0.72, 0.54, 0.33, 1), roughness=0.6, specular=0.35)
mat_wall = create_principled_material("Wall", base_color=(0.96, 0.96, 0.95, 1), roughness=0.9, specular=0.1)
mat_baseboard = create_principled_material("Baseboard", base_color=(0.93, 0.93, 0.93, 1), roughness=0.4, specular=0.2)
mat_black_plastic = create_principled_material("BlackPlastic", base_color=(0.03,0.03,0.03,1), roughness=0.4, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5)
mat_screen = create_principled_material("Screen", base_color=(0.06,0.08,0.1,1), roughness=0.1, specular=0.1)

# -----------------------------

if os.path.exists(chair_path):

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# World light (robust setup even if 'World' is missing)
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    # Remove existing links to Surface to avoid duplicates
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    # Ensure it's linked correctly
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.92, 0.92, 0.92, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.9

# -----------------------------
# Materials
# -----------------------------
wood_floor = create_principled_material("WoodFloor", base_color=(0.82, 0.74, 0.63, 1), roughness=0.8, specular=0.2)
wood_desk = create_principled_material("WoodDesk", base_color=(0.79, 0.63, 0.40, 1), roughness=0.55, specular=0.35)
mat_wall = create_principled_material("Wall", base_color=(0.96, 0.96, 0.95, 1), roughness=0.9, specular=0.1)
mat_baseboard = create_principled_material("Baseboard", base_color=(0.93, 0.93, 0.93, 1), roughness=0.4, specular=0.2)
mat_black_plastic = create_principled_material("BlackPlastic", base_color=(0.03,0.03,0.03,1), roughness=0.4, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5)
mat_screen = create_principled_material("Screen", base_color=(0.06,0.08,0.1,1), roughness=0.1, specular=0.1)

# -----------------------------
# Room: floor, wall, baseboard
# -----------------------------
# Floor
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,0,0))
floor = bpy.context.active_object
floor.name = "Floor"
floor.data.materials.append(wood_floor)

# Wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,-3,1.5))
wall = bpy.context.active_object
wall.name = "Wall"
wall.rotation_euler = Euler((math.radians(90), 0, 0), 'XYZ')
wall.data.materials.append(mat_wall)

# Baseboard along the wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(0,-2.99,0.06))
baseboard = bpy.context.active_object
baseboard.name = "Baseboard"
baseboard.scale = (4.0, 0.01, 0.06)   # 8m long, 2cm thick, 12cm tall
baseboard.data.materials.append(mat_baseboard)

desk_center = Vector((0.0, -2.10, 0.0))
desk_w, desk_d, desk_h = 1.60, 0.75, 0.74
panel_t = 0.04

# Desk top
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_center.y, desk_h + panel_t/2))

for obj in [desk_top]:
    bev = obj.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL')
    bev.width = 0.003

    bev.limit_method = 'ANGLE'

# Left panel

panel_L = bpy.context.active_object

# Right panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x + (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))

panel_R.name = "DeskPanel_R"

panel_R.data.materials.append(wood_desk)

# Modesty panel near the front under the top
desk_front_y = desk_center.y + desk_d/2
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_front_y - 0.15, 0.68))

bevM = modesty.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevM.width=0.0025; bevM.segments=2; bevM.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevM.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# -----------------------------
# Simple laptop
# -----------------------------
# Base (placed from front edge of desk)
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(-0.20, desk_front_y - 0.11, desk_h + 0.015/2))
laptop_base = bpy.context.active_object
laptop_base.name = "LaptopBase"
laptop_base.scale = (0.30/2, 0.22/2, 0.015/2)
laptop_base.data.materials.append(mat_black_plastic)

# Screen (thin slab) slightly open
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(-0.20, desk_front_y - 0.19, desk_h + 0.015 + 0.20/2))
laptop_screen = bpy.context.active_object
laptop_screen.name = "LaptopScreen"
laptop_screen.scale = (0.30/2, 0.01/2, 0.20/2)
laptop_screen.rotation_euler = Euler((math.radians(110), 0, 0), 'XYZ')
laptop_screen.data.materials.append(mat_screen)

# Hinge accent (optional small cylinder)
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cylinder_add(radius=0.005, depth=0.30, location=(-0.20, desk_front_y - 0.17, desk_h + 0.015))

hinge.data.materials.append(mat_black_plastic)

# -----------------------------
# Import office chair (GLB)
# -----------------------------
chair_path = os.path.normpath("output/demo/blendergym_hard/20250926_170545/assets/office chair.glb")
if os.path.exists(chair_path):
    # Import and group
    bpy.ops.import_scene.gltf(filepath=chair_path)
    imported = bpy.context.selected_objects[:]
    chair_coll = bpy.data.collections.new("OfficeChair")

import bpy

def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# Color management for neutral look
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.view_transform = 'Filmic'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.look = 'None'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.exposure = 0.0

# World light (robust setup even if 'World' is missing)
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    # Remove existing links to Surface to avoid duplicates
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    # Ensure it's linked correctly
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.92, 0.92, 0.92, 1.0)

import bpy

from mathutils import Vector, Euler

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# Color management for neutral look
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.view_transform = 'Filmic'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.look = 'None'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.exposure = -0.1

# World light (robust setup even if 'World' is missing)
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    # Remove existing links to Surface to avoid duplicates
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    # Ensure it's linked correctly
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.92, 0.92, 0.92, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.15

# -----------------------------
# Materials
# -----------------------------
wood_floor = create_principled_material("WoodFloor", base_color=(0.78, 0.74, 0.69, 1), roughness=0.85, specular=0.12)
wood_desk = create_principled_material("WoodDesk", base_color=(0.72, 0.52, 0.28, 1), roughness=0.55, specular=0.35)
mat_wall = create_principled_material("Wall", base_color=(0.96, 0.96, 0.95, 1), roughness=0.9, specular=0.1)
mat_baseboard = create_principled_material("Baseboard", base_color=(0.93, 0.93, 0.93, 1), roughness=0.4, specular=0.2)
mat_black_plastic = create_principled_material("BlackPlastic", base_color=(0.03,0.03,0.03,1), roughness=0.4, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5)
mat_screen = create_principled_material("Screen", base_color=(0.06,0.08,0.1,1), roughness=0.1, specular=0.1)

# -----------------------------
# Room: floor, wall, baseboard

# Floor
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,0,0))
floor = bpy.context.active_object
floor.name = "Floor"
floor.data.materials.append(wood_floor)

# Wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,-3,1.5))
wall = bpy.context.active_object
wall.name = "Wall"

# Baseboard along the wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(0,-2.99,0.06))

desk_center = Vector((0.0, -2.10, 0.0))

bevL = panel_L.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevL.width=0.003; bevL.segments=2; bevL.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevL.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Right panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x + (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))
panel_R = bpy.context.active_object
panel_R.name = "DeskPanel_R"
panel_R.scale = (panel_t/2, desk_d/2, desk_h/2)
panel_R.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevR = panel_R.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevR.width=0.003; bevR.segments=2; bevR.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevR.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Modesty panel near the front under the top
desk_front_y = desk_center.y + desk_d/2
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_front_y - 0.15, 0.68))

modesty.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevM = modesty.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevM.width=0.0025; bevM.segments=2; bevM.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevM.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# -----------------------------
# Base (placed from front edge of desk)
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(-0.24, desk_front_y - 0.11, desk_h + 0.015/2))
laptop_base = bpy.context.active_object
laptop_base.name = "LaptopBase"
laptop_base.scale = (0.30/2, 0.22/2, 0.015/2)

# Screen (thin slab) slightly open
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(-0.24, desk_front_y - 0.19, desk_h + 0.015 + 0.20/2))
laptop_screen = bpy.context.active_object

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# Color management for neutral look
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.view_transform = 'Filmic'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.look = 'None'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.exposure = -0.1

# World light (robust setup even if 'World' is missing)
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    # Remove existing links to Surface to avoid duplicates
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    # Ensure it's linked correctly
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.92, 0.92, 0.92, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.15

# -----------------------------
# Materials
# -----------------------------
wood_floor = create_principled_material("WoodFloor", base_color=(0.78, 0.74, 0.69, 1), roughness=0.85, specular=0.12)
wood_desk = create_principled_material("WoodDesk", base_color=(0.72, 0.52, 0.28, 1), roughness=0.55, specular=0.35)
mat_wall = create_principled_material("Wall", base_color=(0.96, 0.96, 0.95, 1), roughness=0.9, specular=0.1)
mat_baseboard = create_principled_material("Baseboard", base_color=(0.93, 0.93, 0.93, 1), roughness=0.4, specular=0.2)
mat_black_plastic = create_principled_material("BlackPlastic", base_color=(0.03,0.03,0.03,1), roughness=0.4, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5)
mat_screen = create_principled_material("Screen", base_color=(0.06,0.08,0.1,1), roughness=0.1, specular=0.1)

# -----------------------------
# Room: floor, wall, baseboard
# -----------------------------
# Floor
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,0,0))
floor = bpy.context.active_object
floor.name = "Floor"
floor.data.materials.append(wood_floor)

# Wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,-3,1.5))
wall = bpy.context.active_object
wall.name = "Wall"
wall.rotation_euler = Euler((math.radians(90), 0, 0), 'XYZ')
wall.data.materials.append(mat_wall)

# Baseboard along the wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(0,-2.99,0.045))

desk_center = Vector((0.0, -2.10, 0.0))

for obj in [desk_top]:
    bev = obj.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL')
    bev.width = 0.003
    bev.segments = 3
    bev.limit_method = 'ANGLE'
    bev.angle_limit = math.radians(30)

# Left panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x - (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))
panel_L = bpy.context.active_object
panel_L.name = "DeskPanel_L"

panel_L.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevL = panel_L.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevL.width=0.003; bevL.segments=2; bevL.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevL.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Right panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x + (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))
panel_R = bpy.context.active_object
panel_R.name = "DeskPanel_R"
panel_R.scale = (panel_t/2, desk_d/2, desk_h/2)
panel_R.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevR = panel_R.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevR.width=0.003; bevR.segments=2; bevR.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevR.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Modesty panel (move to the back side under the top)
desk_front_y = desk_center.y + desk_d/2
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_front_y - 0.15, 0.68))
modesty = bpy.context.active_object
modesty.name = "DeskModesty"
modesty.scale = (desk_w/2 - 0.03, 0.010, 0.30)
modesty.location = Vector((desk_center.x, desk_center.y - desk_d/2 + 0.06, desk_h/2))
modesty.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevM = modesty.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevM.width=0.0025; bevM.segments=2; bevM.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevM.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Front apron under the desktop (thin board at front edge)
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_front_y - 0.04, desk_h - 0.055))
apron = bpy.context.active_object
apron.name = "DeskApronFront"
apron.scale = (desk_w/2 - 0.02, 0.015, 0.055)
apron.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevA = apron.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevA.width=0.0025; bevA.segments=2; bevA.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevA.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# -----------------------------
# Simple laptop

# -----------------------------

def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# Color management for neutral look
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.view_transform = 'Filmic'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.look = 'None'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.exposure = -0.1

# World light (robust setup even if 'World' is missing)
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    # Remove existing links to Surface to avoid duplicates
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    # Ensure it's linked correctly
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.92, 0.92, 0.92, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.18

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# Color management for neutral look
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.view_transform = 'Filmic'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.look = 'None'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.exposure = 0.0

# World light (robust setup even if 'World' is missing)
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    # Remove existing links to Surface to avoid duplicates
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    # Ensure it's linked correctly
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.92, 0.92, 0.92, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.18

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# Color management for neutral look
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.view_transform = 'Filmic'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.look = 'None'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.exposure = 0.0

# World light (robust setup even if 'World' is missing)
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.94, 0.94, 0.94, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.15

# -----------------------------
# Materials
# -----------------------------
wood_floor = create_principled_material("WoodFloor", base_color=(0.74, 0.70, 0.66, 1), roughness=0.65, specular=0.25)
wood_desk = create_principled_material("WoodDesk", base_color=(0.77, 0.60, 0.36, 1), roughness=0.50, specular=0.35)
mat_wall = create_principled_material("Wall", base_color=(0.96, 0.96, 0.95, 1), roughness=0.9, specular=0.1)
mat_baseboard = create_principled_material("Baseboard", base_color=(0.93, 0.93, 0.93, 1), roughness=0.4, specular=0.2)
mat_black_plastic = create_principled_material("BlackPlastic", base_color=(0.03,0.03,0.03,1), roughness=0.4, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5)
mat_screen = create_principled_material("Screen", base_color=(0.06,0.08,0.1,1), roughness=0.1, specular=0.1)

# -----------------------------
# Room: floor, wall, baseboard
# -----------------------------
# Floor
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,0,0))
floor = bpy.context.active_object
floor.name = "Floor"
floor.data.materials.append(wood_floor)

# Wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,-3,1.5))
wall = bpy.context.active_object
wall.name = "Wall"
wall.rotation_euler = Euler((math.radians(90), 0, 0), 'XYZ')
wall.data.materials.append(mat_wall)

# Baseboard along the wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(0,-2.99,0.045))
baseboard = bpy.context.active_object
baseboard.name = "Baseboard"
baseboard.scale = (4.0, 0.015, 0.045)   # ~9 cm tall
baseboard.data.materials.append(mat_baseboard)
baseboard.location.z = 0.045

# -----------------------------

desk_center = Vector((0.0, -2.10, 0.0))
desk_w, desk_d, desk_h = 1.60, 0.75, 0.74
panel_t = 0.04

# Desk top
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_center.y, desk_h + panel_t/2))
desk_top = bpy.context.active_object
desk_top.name = "DeskTop"
desk_top.scale = (desk_w/2, desk_d/2, panel_t/2)
desk_top.data.materials.append(wood_desk)

# Subtle bevels for desk parts
for obj in [desk_top]:
    bev = obj.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL')
    bev.width = 0.004
    bev.segments = 3
    bev.limit_method = 'ANGLE'
    bev.angle_limit = math.radians(30)

# Left panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x - (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))
panel_L = bpy.context.active_object
panel_L.name = "DeskPanel_L"
panel_L.scale = (panel_t/2, desk_d/2, desk_h/2)
panel_L.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevL = panel_L.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevL.width=0.003; bevL.segments=2; bevL.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevL.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Right panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x + (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))
panel_R = bpy.context.active_object
panel_R.name = "DeskPanel_R"
panel_R.scale = (panel_t/2, desk_d/2, desk_h/2)
panel_R.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevR = panel_R.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevR.width=0.003; bevR.segments=2; bevR.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevR.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Modesty panel (move to the back side under the top)
desk_front_y = desk_center.y + desk_d/2
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_front_y - 0.15, 0.68))
modesty = bpy.context.active_object
modesty.name = "DeskModesty"

modesty.location = Vector((desk_center.x, desk_center.y - desk_d/2 + 0.06, desk_h/2))
modesty.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevM = modesty.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevM.width=0.0025; bevM.segments=2; bevM.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevM.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Front apron under the desktop (thin board at front edge)
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_front_y - 0.04, desk_h - 0.040))
apron = bpy.context.active_object
apron.name = "DeskApronFront"

bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(-0.24, desk_front_y - 0.11, desk_h + 0.015/2))
laptop_base = bpy.context.active_object
laptop_base.name = "LaptopBase"
laptop_base.scale = (0.30/2, 0.22/2, 0.015/2)

bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(-0.24, desk_front_y - 0.19, desk_h + 0.015 + 0.20/2))

# Laptop placement and angles to match reference (adjusted)

chair_path = os.path.normpath("output/demo/blendergym_hard/20250926_170545/assets/office chair.glb")
if os.path.exists(chair_path):
    # Import and group
    bpy.ops.import_scene.gltf(filepath=chair_path)
    imported = bpy.context.selected_objects[:]
    chair_coll = bpy.data.collections.new("OfficeChair")
    bpy.context.scene.collection.children.link(chair_coll)
    for obj in imported:

    bpy.ops.object.empty_add(type='PLAIN_AXES', location=(0,0,0))

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in bpy.data.meshes:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.materials:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in bpy.data.images:
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# Color management for neutral look
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.view_transform = 'Filmic'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.look = 'None'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.exposure = 0.0

# World light (robust setup even if 'World' is missing)
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.94, 0.94, 0.94, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.15

# -----------------------------
# Materials
# -----------------------------
wood_floor = create_principled_material("WoodFloor", base_color=(0.74, 0.70, 0.66, 1), roughness=0.65, specular=0.25)
wood_desk = create_principled_material("WoodDesk", base_color=(0.77, 0.60, 0.36, 1), roughness=0.50, specular=0.35)
mat_wall = create_principled_material("Wall", base_color=(0.96, 0.96, 0.95, 1), roughness=0.9, specular=0.1)
mat_baseboard = create_principled_material("Baseboard", base_color=(0.93, 0.93, 0.93, 1), roughness=0.4, specular=0.2)
mat_black_plastic = create_principled_material("BlackPlastic", base_color=(0.03,0.03,0.03,1), roughness=0.4, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5)
mat_screen = create_principled_material("Screen", base_color=(0.06,0.08,0.1,1), roughness=0.1, specular=0.1)

# -----------------------------
# Room: floor, wall, baseboard
# -----------------------------
# Floor
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,0,0))
floor = bpy.context.active_object
floor.name = "Floor"
floor.data.materials.append(wood_floor)

# Wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,-3,1.5))
wall = bpy.context.active_object
wall.name = "Wall"
wall.rotation_euler = Euler((math.radians(90), 0, 0), 'XYZ')
wall.data.materials.append(mat_wall)

# Baseboard along the wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(0,-2.99,0.045))
baseboard = bpy.context.active_object

baseboard.data.materials.append(mat_baseboard)
baseboard.location.z = 0.045

desk_center = Vector((0.0, -2.10, 0.0))
desk_w, desk_d, desk_h = 1.60, 0.75, 0.74

# Desk top
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_center.y, desk_h + panel_t/2))
desk_top = bpy.context.active_object
desk_top.name = "DeskTop"

desk_top.data.materials.append(wood_desk)

# Subtle bevels for desk parts
for obj in [desk_top]:
    bev = obj.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL')
    bev.width = 0.004
    bev.segments = 3
    bev.limit_method = 'ANGLE'
    bev.angle_limit = math.radians(30)

# Left panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x - (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))
panel_L = bpy.context.active_object
panel_L.name = "DeskPanel_L"

panel_L.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevL = panel_L.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevL.width=0.003; bevL.segments=2; bevL.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevL.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Right panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x + (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))

panel_R.name = "DeskPanel_R"
panel_R.scale = (panel_t/2, desk_d/2, desk_h/2)
panel_R.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevR = panel_R.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevR.width=0.003; bevR.segments=2; bevR.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevR.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Modesty panel (move to the back side under the top)
desk_front_y = desk_center.y + desk_d/2
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_front_y - 0.15, 0.68))

modesty.location = Vector((desk_center.x, desk_center.y - desk_d/2 + 0.06, desk_h/2))

# Front apron under the desktop (thin board at front edge)
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_front_y - 0.04, desk_h - 0.040))

laptop_base = bpy.context.active_object

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in list(bpy.data.meshes):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in list(bpy.data.materials):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in list(bpy.data.images):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# Color management for neutral look
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.view_transform = 'Filmic'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.look = 'None'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.exposure = 0.0

# World light (robust setup even if 'World' is missing)
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

# Softer/brighter neutral wall
bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.97, 0.97, 0.965, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.12

# -----------------------------

wood_floor = create_principled_material("WoodFloor", base_color=(0.70, 0.67, 0.63, 1), roughness=0.65, specular=0.25)
wood_desk = create_principled_material("WoodDesk", base_color=(0.77, 0.60, 0.36, 1), roughness=0.50, specular=0.35)
mat_wall = create_principled_material("Wall", base_color=(0.96, 0.96, 0.95, 1), roughness=0.9, specular=0.1)
mat_baseboard = create_principled_material("Baseboard", base_color=(0.93, 0.93, 0.93, 1), roughness=0.4, specular=0.2)
mat_black_plastic = create_principled_material("BlackPlastic", base_color=(0.03,0.03,0.03,1), roughness=0.4, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5)
mat_screen = create_principled_material("Screen", base_color=(0.06,0.08,0.1,1), roughness=0.1, specular=0.1)

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in list(bpy.data.meshes):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in list(bpy.data.materials):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in list(bpy.data.images):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# Color management for neutral look
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.view_transform = 'Filmic'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.look = 'None'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.exposure = 0.0

# World light (robust setup even if 'World' is missing)
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

# Softer/brighter neutral wall
bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.97, 0.97, 0.965, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.12

# -----------------------------
# Materials
# -----------------------------
wood_floor = create_principled_material("WoodFloor", base_color=(0.70, 0.67, 0.63, 1), roughness=0.65, specular=0.25)
wood_desk = create_principled_material("WoodDesk", base_color=(0.77, 0.60, 0.36, 1), roughness=0.50, specular=0.35)
mat_wall = create_principled_material("Wall", base_color=(0.96, 0.96, 0.95, 1), roughness=0.9, specular=0.1)
mat_baseboard = create_principled_material("Baseboard", base_color=(0.93, 0.93, 0.93, 1), roughness=0.4, specular=0.2)
mat_black_plastic = create_principled_material("BlackPlastic", base_color=(0.03,0.03,0.03,1), roughness=0.4, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5)
mat_screen = create_principled_material("Screen", base_color=(0.06,0.08,0.1,1), roughness=0.1, specular=0.1)

# -----------------------------
# Room: floor, wall, baseboard
# -----------------------------
# Floor
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,0,0))
floor = bpy.context.active_object
floor.name = "Floor"
floor.data.materials.append(wood_floor)

# Wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_plane_add(size=8, enter_editmode=False, location=(0,-3,1.5))
wall = bpy.context.active_object
wall.name = "Wall"
wall.rotation_euler = Euler((math.radians(90), 0, 0), 'XYZ')
wall.data.materials.append(mat_wall)

# Baseboard along the wall
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(0,-2.99,0.03))
baseboard = bpy.context.active_object
baseboard.name = "Baseboard"
baseboard.scale = (4.0, 0.015, 0.030)   # ~6 cm tall
baseboard.data.materials.append(mat_baseboard)
baseboard.location.z = 0.030

# -----------------------------
# Desk (simple parametric build)
# -----------------------------
desk_center = Vector((0.0, -2.10, 0.0))
desk_w, desk_d, desk_h = 1.60, 0.75, 0.74
panel_t = 0.04

# Desk top
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_center.y, desk_h + panel_t/2))
desk_top = bpy.context.active_object
desk_top.name = "DeskTop"
desk_top.scale = (desk_w/2, desk_d/2, panel_t/2)
desk_top.data.materials.append(wood_desk)

# Subtle bevels for desk parts
for obj in [desk_top]:
    bev = obj.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL')
    bev.width = 0.004
    bev.segments = 3
    bev.limit_method = 'ANGLE'
    bev.angle_limit = math.radians(30)

# Left panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x - (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))
panel_L = bpy.context.active_object
panel_L.name = "DeskPanel_L"
panel_L.scale = (panel_t/2, desk_d/2, desk_h/2)
panel_L.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevL = panel_L.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevL.width=0.003; bevL.segments=2; bevL.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevL.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Right panel
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x + (desk_w/2 - panel_t/2), desk_center.y, desk_h/2))
panel_R = bpy.context.active_object
panel_R.name = "DeskPanel_R"
panel_R.scale = (panel_t/2, desk_d/2, desk_h/2)
panel_R.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevR = panel_R.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevR.width=0.003; bevR.segments=2; bevR.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevR.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Modesty panel (move to the back side under the top)
desk_front_y = desk_center.y + desk_d/2
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_front_y - 0.15, 0.68))
modesty = bpy.context.active_object
modesty.name = "DeskModesty"
modesty.scale = (desk_w/2 - 0.03, 0.010, 0.30)
modesty.location = Vector((desk_center.x, desk_center.y - desk_d/2 + 0.06, desk_h/2))
modesty.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevM = modesty.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevM.width=0.0025; bevM.segments=2; bevM.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevM.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# Front apron under the desktop (thin board at front edge)
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(desk_center.x, desk_front_y - 0.04, desk_h - 0.040))
apron = bpy.context.active_object
apron.name = "DeskApronFront"
apron.scale = (desk_w/2 - 0.02, 0.015, 0.035)
apron.location.z = desk_h - 0.040
apron.data.materials.append(wood_desk)
bevA = apron.modifiers.new(name="Bevel", type='BEVEL'); bevA.width=0.0025; bevA.segments=2; bevA.limit_method='ANGLE'; bevA.angle_limit=math.radians(30)

# -----------------------------
# Simple laptop
# -----------------------------
# Base (placed from front edge of desk)
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(-0.24, desk_front_y - 0.11, desk_h + 0.015/2))
laptop_base = bpy.context.active_object
laptop_base.name = "LaptopBase"
laptop_base.scale = (0.30/2, 0.22/2, 0.015/2)
laptop_base.data.materials.append(mat_black_plastic)

# Screen (thin slab) slightly open
bpy.ops.mesh.primitive_cube_add(size=1, location=(-0.24, desk_front_y - 0.19, desk_h + 0.015 + 0.20/2))

laptop_screen.name = "LaptopScreen"
laptop_screen.scale = (0.30/2, 0.01/2, 0.20/2)
laptop_screen.rotation_euler = Euler((math.radians(110), 0, 0), 'XYZ')
laptop_screen.data.materials.append(mat_screen)

# Hinge accent (optional small cylinder)

# Laptop placement and angles to match reference (adjusted)
laptop_base.location.x = -0.26

laptop_base.rotation_euler.z = math.radians(-8)

laptop_screen.location.x = -0.26
laptop_screen.location.y = laptop_base.location.y - 0.10
laptop_screen.rotation_euler.x = math.radians(106)
laptop_screen.rotation_euler.z = math.radians(-8)

hinge.location.x = -0.26
hinge.location.y = (laptop_base.location.y + laptop_screen.location.y)/2
hinge.rotation_euler.z = math.radians(-8)

# -----------------------------

chair_path = os.path.normpath("output/demo/blendergym_hard/20250926_170545/assets/office chair.glb")
if os.path.exists(chair_path):
    # Import and group
    bpy.ops.import_scene.gltf(filepath=chair_path)
    imported = bpy.context.selected_objects[:]
    chair_coll = bpy.data.collections.new("OfficeChair")
    bpy.context.scene.collection.children.link(chair_coll)
    for obj in imported:
        chair_coll.objects.link(obj)

    # Create an empty to manipulate the whole chair as one
    bpy.ops.object.empty_add(type='PLAIN_AXES', location=(0,0,0))

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in list(bpy.data.meshes):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in list(bpy.data.materials):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in list(bpy.data.images):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# Color management
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.view_transform = 'Filmic'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.look = 'None'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.exposure = 0.0

# World light
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.97, 0.97, 0.965, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.12

wood_desk = create_principled_material("WoodDesk", base_color=(0.77, 0.60, 0.36, 1), roughness=0.50, specular=0.35)

import bpy
import math
from mathutils import Vector, Euler
import os

# -----------------------------
# Helpers
# -----------------------------
def clear_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for block in list(bpy.data.meshes):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.meshes.remove(block)
    for block in list(bpy.data.materials):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.materials.remove(block)
    for block in list(bpy.data.images):
        if block.users == 0:
            bpy.data.images.remove(block)

def create_principled_material(name, base_color=(1,1,1,1), roughness=0.5, metallic=0.0, specular=0.5):
    mat = bpy.data.materials.new(name)
    mat.use_nodes = True
    bsdf = mat.node_tree.nodes.get("Principled BSDF")
    bsdf.inputs["Base Color"].default_value = base_color
    bsdf.inputs["Roughness"].default_value = roughness
    bsdf.inputs["Metallic"].default_value = metallic
    bsdf.inputs["Specular"].default_value = specular
    return mat

def look_at(obj, target=Vector((0,0,0))):
    direction = target - obj.location
    rot_quat = direction.to_track_quat('-Z', 'Y')
    obj.rotation_euler = rot_quat.to_euler()

clear_scene()

# -----------------------------
# Scene settings
# -----------------------------
bpy.context.scene.render.engine = 'CYCLES'
bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 128
bpy.context.scene.cycles.use_adaptive_sampling = True
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_x = 1024
bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_y = 1024
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 1.0

# Color management
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.view_transform = 'Filmic'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.look = 'None'
bpy.context.scene.view_settings.exposure = 0.0

# World light
if bpy.context.scene.world is None:
    world = bpy.data.worlds.new("World")
    bpy.context.scene.world = world
world = bpy.context.scene.world
world.use_nodes = True
nt = world.node_tree
nodes = nt.nodes
bg = nodes.get("Background")
if bg is None:
    bg = nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeBackground")
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if getattr(l.to_node, "bl_idname", "") == "ShaderNodeOutputWorld" and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))
else:
    out = nodes.get("World Output") or nodes.new(type="ShaderNodeOutputWorld")
    for l in list(nt.links):
        if l.to_node == out and l.to_socket == out.inputs.get("Surface"):
            nt.links.remove(l)
    nt.links.new(bg.outputs.get("Background"), out.inputs.get("Surface"))

bg.inputs[0].default_value = (0.97, 0.97, 0.965, 1.0)
bg.inputs[1].default_value = 0.18
